/*
This file is used to specify the configurations for Babel. 

Babel is a transpiler that converts modern JavaScript (ES6+) code into an older JavaScript version (e.g., ES5) to ensure compatibility with environments (browsers, older Node.js versions) that do not support certain modern JavaScript syntax (e.g., let, const, arrow functions, async/await, import/export).

- Use .babelrc when you need configuration scoped to specific directories or parts of a project. If placed in the root directory, configurations will apply globally to the entire project, including its subdirectories.

- Use babel.config.js for a global, project-wide configuration, especially useful in larger projects or monorepos.

*/

{
  "presets": ["@babel/preset-env"]
}
